  "keywords": "Main, Normal, sweet potatoes, chickpeas, chicken, coconut milk",
  "name": "Coconut chicken Curry Recipe",
  "recipeIngredient": [
    "3 medium sweet potatoes, chopped",
    "1 medium onion, chopped",
    "2 cans chickpeas, drained",
    "1 tbsp ginger",
    "4 tbsp red curry paste",
    "1 tsp cayenne pepper",
    "2 chicken breasts, chopped",
    "Juice and zest from 1 lime",
    "1 jar coconut milk",
    "1 bunch cilantro",
    "2 fresh jalapenos",
    "1 cauliflower",
    "Blend lime juice, coconut milk, and cilantro stems. Set aside. Boil sweet potato 6 minutes. While cooking, sautee onions in 2 tbsp oil or butter over medium heat. Add in potatoes and cook 8 minutes. Add ginger, curry paste, and cayenne pepper and stir. Add in chickpeas and chicken (salt and pepper chicken beforehand) and cook 5 minutes. Add in coconut milk mixture and simmer until chicken is cooked through. Season with salt, add in jalapeno, and add 0.25 cup chopped cilantro. Mix in cauliflower rice.",
    "For the rice:",
    "Cut 1 head into florets and add to a food processor (do 2-3 batches if food processor isn't very big). Pulse until cauliflower is around couscous sized. Add oil to a pan over medium high heat and cook stirring occasionally, 5 minutes."
  ],
